<html xmlns:MadCap="http://www.madcapsoftware.com/Schemas/MadCap.xsd" MadCap:conditions="Products.Lingo" MadCap:lastBlockDepth="4" MadCap:lastHeight="165" MadCap:lastWidth="1212">
    <body>
        <p>You can flatten snippets and variables when creating a new project, or you (or the translator)&#160;can update an existing project's flattening settings on the <span class="Emphasis">Flare Settings</span> tab of the Project Properties dialog (<span class="Emphasis">File&gt;Project Properties</span>). The settings are the same in both locations.</p>
        <ul>
            <li><span class="SetOffFirstLevel">Flatten a Variable </span>Select the variable set(s) you want to flatten from the grid on the left side of the dialog. Then select or deselect individual variables from the grid on the right side of the dialog. If you want to replace variable definitions for a specific target, you can optionally select a target from the <span class="Emphasis">Filter to target</span> drop-down.</li>
            <li><span class="SetOffFirstLevel">Flatten a Snippet </span>Select <span class="Emphasis">Convert sub-segment snippets to text</span> at the bottom of the dialog. This will convert all inline snippets to text. </li>
        </ul>
    </body>
</html>